---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Terms of Service"
	description="Terms of Service for alienzj's personal tools and vdirsyncer integration."
	pubDate={new Date('2026-04-22')}
    category="Legal"
>
	<div class="legal-container">
		<p>
            By using the Google Cloud API integration provided by <strong>alienzj</strong> for 
            <strong>vdirsyncer</strong>, you agree to the following terms.
		</p>

		<section>
			<h2>1. Purpose of Use</h2>
			<p>
				This application is provided for personal use only. It is intended to allow 
                the synchronization of personal data (such as Google Calendar) with 
                local clients using the <code>vdirsyncer</code> CLI tool.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>2. Disclaimer of Warranty</h2>
			<p>
				The software and API configuration are provided "as is", without warranty 
                of any kind, express or implied. In no event shall the author be liable 
                for any claim, damages, or other liability arising from the use of this tool.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>3. Responsibility</h2>
			<p>
				You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your own 
                credentials and for all activities that occur under your Google account.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>4. Changes to Terms</h2>
			<p>
				The author reserves the right to modify these terms at any time. 
                Continued use of the integration constitutes acceptance of the new terms.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>5. Governing Law</h2>
			<p>
				These terms are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of 
                the jurisdiction in which the author resides.
			</p>
		</section>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style>
	.legal-container {
		max-width: 720px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	section {
		margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
	}

	h2 {
		font-size: 1.2rem;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
		color: var(--text-muted);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
		padding-bottom: var(--space-2);
		margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
	}

    p {
        margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    }
</style>
